@startuml
title From ideal conditions to the closed-form option value
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #EAF6F0
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #2E8B67
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #F5FBF8
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #2E8B67
skinparam ArrowColor #2E8B67

start
:Assume ideal market conditions\n(constant r, lognormal stock, no dividends);
:Build hedged position\n1 share long, 1/w1 options short;
:Rebalance continuously\nto keep the value riskless;
:Set hedged return equal to r\n(no-arbitrage condition);
:Derive the differential equation\nw2 = rw - r x w1 - 1/2 v2 x2 w11;
:Apply maturity boundary condition\nw(x,t*) = max(x - c, 0);
:Substitute variables\nto reach the heat equation y2 = y11;
:Solve with the Gaussian kernel\nand substitute back;
:Read off the closed form\nw = x N(d1) - c e^r(t-t*) N(d2);
stop
@enduml
